{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:20:51.758Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1779542451758_1","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-037\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-05-23\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `src/cypherclaw/tuning/system.py`\n- `src/cypherclaw/tuning/__init__.py`\n- `tests/test_tuning_system.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `tuning_for_name()` correctly resolves both canonical tuning names (e.g., \"twelve_tet\") and legacy aliases (e.g., \"12-TET\", \"12tet\", \"equal-temperament\"). The resolution is case-insensitive and handles normalization of dashes and spaces to underscores.\n\nThe frequencies generated by the resulting `TwelveTET` instance match the expected 12-TET equal temperament values.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation covers all requested legacy aliases and provides a robust factory for future tunings. Parametrized tests in `tests/test_tuning_system.py` ensure comprehensive coverage of the alias space.\n\n## Consistency\nThe `tuning_for_name` factory follows the established pattern in the `cypherclaw.tuning` package and is properly exported. While `midi_scene.py` maintains its own legacy normalization logic, this is consistent with its role as a \"faithful MIDI\" transmitter, and the new factory provides the necessary bridge for the new pitch pipeline.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues were identified. The implementation uses standard string normalization and dictionary lookups.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured, typed, and documented. The tests are clear and cover edge cases (unknown tunings).\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No blocking or minor issues found.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation successfully provides the requested backward compatibility for legacy 12-TET scenes. The redundancy with `midi_scene.py`'s internal normalization is noted but acceptable given the separate roles of the two components.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-037-verify.md"}}
{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-05-23T13:20:51.766Z","tool_id":"update_topic_1779542451558_0","status":"success","output":"## 📂 Topic: **Creating Verification Report**\n\n**Summary:**\nI have completed the research and testing for T-037. I confirmed that `tuning_for_name` is correctly implemented in `src/cypherclaw/tuning/system.py` and exported via `__init__.py`. It successfully handles legacy 12-TET aliases like \"12-TET\", \"12tet\", and \"equal-temperament\" by resolving them to the `TwelveTET` class. I verified this with thorough regression tests that cover canonical names, legacy aliases, and unknown names. The full test suite passed without regressions. I am now ready to issue the verification report.\n\n> [!STRATEGY]\n> **Intent:** Creating the verification report for T-037."}
